# Foozi – SEO Page Architecture

Version: 1.0
Status: Core Growth Infrastructure
Owner: Product / SEO
Last Updated: 2026-03-13

---

# Objective

The SEO architecture enables Foozi to scale content across thousands of football matches, teams, and competitions.

Goals:

Generate search traffic
Capture match-related search intent
Create a scalable internal linking structure

Primary traffic sources:

Match predictions
Team statistics
Head-to-head comparisons
League overviews

---

# Core Page Types

The platform should generate the following page types:

1. Match Pages
2. Prediction Pages
3. Team Pages
4. League Pages
5. Head-to-Head Pages
6. Daily Match Hubs

---

# 1. Match Pages

Purpose:

Capture match-specific search traffic.

URL structure:

/match/arsenal-vs-liverpool

Example search queries:

Arsenal vs Liverpool prediction
Arsenal Liverpool stats
Arsenal Liverpool lineup

Page content:

Match header
Tactra prediction
Match stats
Team comparison
Head-to-head
Lineups
AI match analysis

Internal links:

Team pages
League page
Head-to-head page

---

# 2. Prediction Pages

Purpose:

Capture betting-related searches.

URL structure:

/prediction/arsenal-vs-liverpool

Example queries:

Arsenal vs Liverpool prediction
Arsenal Liverpool betting tips
Arsenal Liverpool odds prediction

Content structure:

Tactra prediction model
Match insights
Team form
AI match analysis

These pages may overlap with match pages but focus on prediction intent.

---

# 3. Team Pages

Purpose:

High-volume evergreen traffic.

URL structure:

/team/arsenal

Example queries:

Arsenal stats
Arsenal form
Arsenal next match

Content:

Team overview
Recent matches
Team form
Season statistics
Upcoming fixtures

Internal links:

Match pages
League page

---

# 4. League Pages

Purpose:

Capture competition-level traffic.

URL structure:

/league/premier-league

Example queries:

Premier League stats
Premier League matches today
Premier League predictions

Content:

League table
Top matches
Top teams
League statistics

Internal links:

Team pages
Match pages

---

# 5. Head-to-Head Pages

Purpose:

Extremely strong SEO traffic driver.

URL structure:

/h2h/arsenal-vs-liverpool

Example queries:

Arsenal vs Liverpool head to head
Arsenal Liverpool history
Arsenal Liverpool record

Content:

Historical matches
Win statistics
Goals comparison

Internal links:

Match page
Team pages

---

# 6. Daily Match Hub

Purpose:

Capture daily search intent.

URL structure:

/matches/today

Example queries:

Football matches today
Premier League matches today
Soccer fixtures today

Content:

Matches grouped by league
Top matches highlighted
Links to match pages

---

# Internal Linking Strategy

Internal linking is critical for SEO authority.

Match pages should link to:

Team pages
League pages
Head-to-head pages

Team pages should link to:

Recent matches
Upcoming matches
League page

League pages should link to:

Top matches
Team pages

---

# Content Automation

Most pages should be automatically generated using data feeds.

AI content should generate:

Match insights
Stat explanations
Short match previews

Automation allows thousands of pages to be updated daily.

---

# Structured Data (Schema)

Pages should include structured data for search engines.

Match pages:

SportsEvent schema

Team pages:

SportsTeam schema

League pages:

SportsOrganization schema

---

# SEO Keywords Strategy

Target search intents:

Match predictions
Team statistics
Head-to-head comparisons
Match schedules

Example keywords:

Arsenal vs Liverpool prediction
Bayern vs Dortmund stats
Barcelona next match

